A unit test shouldn’t:

🚫 Call a DB
🚫 Run a browser
🚫 Make an HTTP call
🚫 Rely on stuff on other machines

A unit test should pass without a network connection.

There’s nothing wrong with doing such things in a test. But if a test does these things, it’s not a unit test.

This is one of the drawbacks of decentralization.

Without a central authority, determining who is who, is nearly impossible. Maybe each person becomes their own central authority — good luck bootstrapping that chain of trust.

Just sharing this because I just now needed to implement bit flags and I instinctively avoided enums, but then it ended up being messier w/o them which led me to this realization

But yeah enums bad

I wish tho that the bitwise op types were smarter. In the permission enum im only using the first 10 bits , so instead of typing return of bitwise ops as `number`, it should be the range of numbers expressable by bitwise ORing all the enum variants which is 1->511 in this case

But if you use enums for bit flags you're going to be using bitwise operations (which return `number`) to combine them, so it makes sense that an enum and `number` are assignable to each other https://t.co/hXRc35oIcG

The $PORT above reads the PORT env variable.

You can pass env vars on the command line too:

A #webperf thought:

Look at the different parts of the DOM tree & JS that your users get. Do they look like...

1. Your mental model as a dev
2. Your org-chart, how your teams are set up
3. How users experience your site

If it's not (3), perhaps your tools are wasteful?

Every time you make a selection, it is instantly filled with your foreground color! It even works on layers that have transparency locked! --> Check out the video demo above in the header/image area for this product (just tap through to the second image).IMPORTANT NOTE! This plugin has only been tested for the latest Photoshop CC versions (CC 2021, 2022 updates). It might work on earlier versions, but I cannot guarantee that it will.Questions? Find me on Twitter.Enjoy this plugin and if you like it, please leave a rating! - Kyle
